table_trans: Director of Education (Pr.) Maharashtra State, Pune

The functions and functions of the State Level Committee are: - 1) To review the policy decision regarding Pradhan Mantri Poshan Shakti Nirman Yojana. 2) To ensure implementation of the guidelines of the Central Government. 3) To review and guide the measures taken by the Department on the quality of nutrition, enhancement of nutritional value. 4) To review the funds received from the Central Government. 5) To plan the implementation of the proposal pending with the Central Government. 6) To coordinate with the administrative departments working on the implementation of the scheme. The Expert Members and other representatives shall be selected by the Principal Secretary (School Education). The Committee shall meet at least once in a year.
District Level Representative of Food Corporation of India
4 expert members on nutrition, child education and health (out of which 2 are women members)
Group Education Officer / Superintendent (PM POSHAN) of 3 to 4 Taluks

The functions and functions of the District Level Committee are 1) to conduct regular health check-ups of the students as well as to review the supply of Aryan-folic acid and disinfectant tablets to the students. 2) to check the nutritional value of the food served to the students. 3) to take necessary measures to ensure the availability of quality, clean, safe and nutritious food to the students.

The functions and functions of the Taluk Samiti are: - 1) To review the food grain supply at the school level. 2) To ensure clean, hygienic and nutritious food to the students. 3) To review the funds received by the schools from the State Government. 4) To review the training of cooks and helpers. 5) To coordinate with the Taluk Offices working towards implementation of the scheme.
